.TH COHCC 1 "2025-07-17" "Cohesix v1.0" "Cohesix Project"
.SH NAME
cohcc \- Cohesix compiler frontend
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cohcc build source.c -o out [--backend=tcc|zig]
.RI [ --trace ]
.RI [ --sandbox-info ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cohcc
invokes an auditable C compiler in a reproducible manner. Output paths are
restricted to the project directory or \fI/mnt/data\fR and the binary is always
statically linked. The selected backend is logged to
\fI/log/cohcc_invocations.log\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --trace
write the full compiler command to the log.
.TP
.B --sandbox-info
print filesystem and role sandbox details then exit.
.TP
.B --backend
select the compiler backend (default \fBtcc\fR).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /log/cohcc_invocations.log
command history and diagnostics.
.TP
.I /log/cohcc_fail.log
error details on failed builds.
.SH EXAMPLES
Compile a C program using zig:
.P
.B cohcc build hello.c -o /mnt/data/hello --backend=zig
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR zig (1)
